text: Nasib (Fate) is a 1949 black-and-white romantic drama film from Singapore. It was directed by B. S. Rajhans and stars S. Roomai Noor, Siput Sarawak, Daeng Harris, and P. Ramlee. It was one of eight popular films made by Shaw Brothers Studio in the 1940s. ==See also== * P. Ramlee filmography ==References==
title: Nasib
